---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Section from '../../components/primitives/Section.astro';
import Eyebrow from '../../components/primitives/Eyebrow.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  lane="shared"
  title="Privacy policy"
  description="Privacy policy for S.Prestige Services — Kissonerga, Pafos, Cyprus."
>
  <Section width="narrow">
    <Eyebrow>Legal</Eyebrow>
    <h1 class="mt-3 font-display text-4xl text-fg md:text-5xl">Privacy policy</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-fg-muted">Last updated: 30 April 2026</p>

    <div class="mt-10 space-y-10 text-fg-muted leading-relaxed [&_h2]:font-display [&_h2]:text-xl [&_h2]:text-fg [&_h2]:mb-3 [&_h2]:mt-0 [&_h3]:font-display [&_h3]:text-base [&_h3]:text-fg [&_h3]:mt-4 [&_h3]:mb-2 [&_p]:text-sm [&_li]:text-sm [&_ul]:list-disc [&_ul]:pl-5 [&_ul]:space-y-1 [&_strong]:text-fg [&_strong]:font-medium">

      <section>
        <h2>Who we are</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>S.Prestige Services</strong> — automotive services business
          based in Kissonerga, Pafos. We are the controller of personal data
          collected through this website and through your contact with our
          team.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Eustathios Plaza, Leoforos Chrisoneras, Kat.5, Kissonerga,
          Pafos 8574, Cyprus.<br/>
          WhatsApp <a href="tel:+35796471717" class="text-gold hover:text-gold-soft">+357 96 471717</a> — primary contact for any data request.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>What this policy covers</h2>
        <p>
          This page explains what personal data we collect when you contact
          us for detailing, mechanical service, recovery, buy &amp; sell,
          transfers or rentals; how we use it, how long we keep it, and what
          rights you have under the EU General Data Protection Regulation
          (GDPR) and Cyprus Law 125(I)/2018 on the Protection of Natural
          Persons with regard to the Processing of Personal Data.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Data we collect</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Contact details</strong> — name, phone number, occasionally email — given when you first message us on WhatsApp or call.</li>
          <li><strong>Vehicle details</strong> — make, model, year, registration plate, mileage, description of condition or fault — given so we can quote.</li>
          <li><strong>Photos and short videos</strong> of your vehicle if you send them for a valuation, to describe damage, headlight yellowing or interior state.</li>
          <li><strong>For rentals</strong> — a copy of your passport or national ID, driving licence, and a credit-card pre-authorisation as deposit. Required by Cypriot insurance and tourist-vehicle regulations.</li>
          <li><strong>For airport transfers</strong> — arrival flight number and time, name of the lead passenger, drop-off address.</li>
          <li><strong>Communication content</strong> — your WhatsApp messages and SMS, our replies, call notes where relevant.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">
          We do not collect marketing identifiers, social-media profiling
          data, or anything beyond what you actively send us. We do not
          sell your data.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Why we use your data (lawful basis under GDPR)</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Contract</strong> — quoting, booking and providing the service you requested.</li>
          <li><strong>Legal obligation</strong> — insurance paperwork for rentals, vehicle-handover records, VAT invoicing.</li>
          <li><strong>Legitimate interest</strong> — replying to your follow-up questions, keeping a service history so we can help you faster next time.</li>
          <li><strong>Consent</strong> — only for direct marketing, and only if you opt in.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Who else sees your data</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>WhatsApp / Meta</strong> — when you message us, your message is routed through Meta's servers, including transfer to the United States. Meta is the controller of that routing; their privacy policy applies in parallel to ours.</li>
          <li><strong>Vercel</strong> — our website host (United States). Standard server logs only; we do not run profiling analytics on visitors.</li>
          <li><strong>Google</strong> — the embedded map on our contact page is served by Google Maps. When the map loads, your IP is sent to Google.</li>
          <li><strong>Insurance brokers</strong> — when you rent a vehicle, we share the data required by the insurer to bind the cover.</li>
          <li><strong>Cypriot tax authorities</strong> — invoice data when you request a VAT receipt, as required by law.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">
          We do not share your data with advertising networks.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>International transfers</h2>
        <p>
          WhatsApp/Meta and Vercel transfer data to the United States. Both
          rely on European Commission Standard Contractual Clauses (SCCs)
          as the transfer mechanism, supplemented by their own security
          measures.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>How long we keep your data</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>WhatsApp threads</strong> — kept within the WhatsApp Business app for as long as useful for service history (typically up to 3 years).</li>
          <li><strong>Rental ID and licence copies</strong> — for the duration of the rental plus 3 years (insurance / damage-claim window).</li>
          <li><strong>Buy &amp; sell vehicle photos and listings</strong> — until the vehicle is sold or the listing withdrawn, plus up to 12 months of archive.</li>
          <li><strong>Tax and accounting records</strong> — 6 years (Cyprus VAT Law).</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">
          When the retention period ends, we delete the data, or anonymise
          it where we need to keep statistics.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Your rights</h2>
        <p>You can ask us to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Confirm what data we hold about you (right of access)</li>
          <li>Correct anything inaccurate (rectification)</li>
          <li>Delete what we are not legally required to keep (erasure)</li>
          <li>Restrict processing while we resolve a dispute (restriction)</li>
          <li>Receive your data in a portable format (portability)</li>
          <li>Object to processing based on legitimate interest (objection)</li>
          <li>Withdraw consent at any time, where consent is the basis</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Send any of these requests to WhatsApp <a href="tel:+35796471717" class="text-gold hover:text-gold-soft">+357 96 471717</a> or by post to the address above. We respond within 30 days, as required by GDPR.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Complaints</h2>
        <p>
          If you believe we have mishandled your data, you can complain to
          the Cypriot supervisory authority:
        </p>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Office of the Commissioner for Personal Data Protection<br/>
          1, Iasonos Street, 1082 Nicosia, Cyprus<br/>
          +357 22 818 456 · commissioner@dataprotection.gov.cy
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          This website uses no third-party tracking or advertising cookies.
          The embedded Google Map may set Google's own cookies when you
          scroll into it. The site itself only uses functional cookies
          required for the page to load.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this policy as the business or applicable law
          changes. The "last updated" date at the top will reflect any
          change.
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </Section>
</BaseLayout>
